[[Image:MargaretHamiltoninTheWizardOfOz.jpg|thumb|right|550px|The Wicked Witch as portrayed by [[Margaret Hamilton]] in the 1939 film ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'']]
 
In the classic movie ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'', the Wicked Witch, played by actress [[Margaret Hamilton]], was stooped, green-skinned, and dressed entirely in black with a black pointed hat upon her head. In many people's minds, this representation of the Wicked Witch has become an [[archetype]] for human wickedness.
